ENCEPHALITIS - NEPAL (02)
*************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.healthnet.org/programs/promed.html>
See Also
Encephalitis - Nepal 980824225028
Date: Wed, 16 Sep 1998 18:18:54 -0500
Source: Kathmandu Post, 16 September 1998
Via: Clyde Markon <docmarkon@worldnet.att.net>

Fifty encephalitis cases have been found in course of medical examinations
of patients in Janakpur zonal hospital, private nursing homes and private
clinics of Janakpur. Although exact data were not available in Janakpur
zonal hospital, it is learnt from Dr Ram Pariskshan Yadav of the hospital
that 15 encephalitis patients were admitted to this hospital during this
month. Similarly, 7 patients were admitted to Care Medical Centre, of whom
5 were cured while two were referred to B.P. Memorial medical college. In
the same way, 10 encephalitis patients were admitted to Janakpur medical
centre, a nursing home located at Mills Area. Asked in this connection,
officials in Janakpur public health office said they had no information in
this regard.
According to Care Medical Centre, three people suffering from meningitis
were also admitted in this nursing home and returned home after recovering
from the disease.
